Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.67,0:01:38.49,main,instructor knight,0,0,0,,You're falling behind, Lucius!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.49,0:01:39.38,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.92,0:01:44.25,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please, Prince Theodore.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.55,0:01:48.25,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,Don't you think you're \Nmaking use of me in the wrong way?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.60,0:01:52.88,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,You said you want to join the knight \Ncandidates' training as a man, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.88,0:01:55.15,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,I'm not sure that's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.15,0:01:57.80,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,Why should I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.80,0:02:00.96,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,You sent me a letter the \Nother day, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.96,0:02:02.76,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,It said I could rely on your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.76,0:02:05.77,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,Yes, I wrote that! I wrote that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.60,0:02:09.20,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,But why do you need to\N sneak in to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.20,0:02:11.83,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,You could just have a knight \Nassigned to instruct you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.83,0:02:14.31,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,If I did that, they'd surely \Ntry to be considerate of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.31,0:02:16.78,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,and I want to be trained without any mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.78,0:02:20.86,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,Unbelievable. To think you'd willingly \Nchoose to go and be treated harshly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.86,0:02:22.20,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,I could never do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.64,0:02:24.63,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.48,0:02:29.60,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.60,0:02:33.30,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,Very well! I shall assist \Nmy lovely older sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.30,0:02:37.07,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,I will exert every effort \Nto make your wish come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.07,0:02:39.93,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Um, why the sudden change?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.93,0:02:42.80,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,Well, it seems entertaining, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.27,0:02:46.40,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,I think that even my older brother \Nwould never be able to anticipate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.40,0:02:49.92,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,Who'd ever think, "My wife is going to \Ndress as a man to infiltrate the knights"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.92,0:02:53.88,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,How could I not take the opportunity \Nto surprise my brother like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.88,0:02:58.36,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,It isn't as though I'm doing this\Nto shock Prince Arnold, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.73,0:03:06.94,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,I would love to see the look \Non my brother's face, whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.14,0:03:13.07,main,instructor knight,0,0,0,,That's enough for today! Dismissed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.07,0:03:14.73,main,knight candidates,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.96,0:03:21.07,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,This is Galkhein's basic training?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.07,0:03:23.21,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Lucius?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:28.75,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Fritz. Thanks, but I'll be all \Nright after I rest a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.75,0:03:30.45,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,I'll join you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.45,0:03:33.09,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,Even if I head back to the \Ninn, I'll just be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.09,0:03:33.90,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Inn?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.24,0:03:36.64,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,I came here from Ceutena.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.64,0:03:39.98,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,Have you heard of it? It's \Na port town in the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.98,0:03:43.01,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,That's where ships from \NCoyolles dock, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:45.38,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,Yes, it's a great town.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.38,0:03:47.28,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,If I didn't look up to that person so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.28,0:03:51.34,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,I'd never have aimed to be a knight, and I'd \Nprobably have lived my whole life in that town.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.34,0:03:52.59,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,That person?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.59,0:03:54.04,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.92,0:03:56.42,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,The war hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.42,0:03:57.90,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,Master of the sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.90,0:03:59.51,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,He's just so amazing, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.51,0:04:00.55,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.55,0:04:04.64,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,I want to become a great knight, \Njust like Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.64,0:04:05.68,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,You there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.16,0:04:09.20,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,You mustn't refer to members of the \Nimperial family in that manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.20,0:04:12.39,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,You must be careful to call him \NHis Highness, the crown prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.39,0:04:13.82,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.21,0:04:15.42,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,As long as you understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.42,0:04:16.62,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Raise your heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.11,0:04:20.66,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,You're... Count Lawvine!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.44,0:04:23.35,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,His Lordship, Count Lawvine?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.35,0:04:27.24,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He's the guardian of the north and a loyal \Nretainer to the Galkhein imperial family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.24,0:04:28.33,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But three years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.68,0:04:30.90,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold, who will have become emperor,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.90,0:04:33.34,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,will declare him a monstrous \Ncriminal, and he'll be slaughtered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.11,0:04:37.58,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,H-Has he noticed \NI'm only dressed as a ma—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.58,0:04:39.92,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Do you like to eat chicken?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.92,0:04:40.59,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.88,0:04:42.90,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.90,0:04:45.76,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,I see. In that case, you \Nshould eat more of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.20,0:04:50.79,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,From what I can see, you have less \Nmuscle mass than the average man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.79,0:04:52.10,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.73,0:04:55.78,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Starting tomorrow, I will \Nbe joining your instructors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.78,0:04:56.92,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,I look forward to working with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.92,0:04:57.73,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.58,0:05:02.20,main,knight 1,0,0,0,,Your Lordship, it's nearly time for your \Naudience with His Majesty, the emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.20,0:05:03.74,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll go immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.09,0:05:05.47,main,Lawvine,0,0,0,,If you'll excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.47,0:05:06.76,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.85,0:05:08.36,main,Fritz,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.16,0:05:37.75,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Elsie, I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:38.90,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.07,0:05:49.46,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.46,0:05:50.66,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.04,0:05:53.36,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Were you able to sleep last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.36,0:05:54.16,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.02,0:05:58.03,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.67,0:06:03.55,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Tomorrow afternoon at two, \Ncome to the western back gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.28,0:06:06.05,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Don't let anyone see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:10.80,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Should I dye my hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.80,0:06:12.55,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,No, that isn't necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:16.52,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I see. Then, I will arrive in clothes \Nthat will look natural in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.98,0:06:24.07,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Um, Lady Rishe?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.07,0:06:25.07,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.07,0:06:28.07,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Why were you speaking \Nsecretly with Prince Arnold?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.53,0:06:31.32,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,The truth is that the prince and \NI are going into town tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.63,0:06:34.83,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,What sort of business is taking you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.84,0:06:38.96,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm certain it must be some \Nsort of official business.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.81,0:06:42.39,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It would be best to wear \Nsomething that won't stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.39,0:06:45.34,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,A brown linen dress and a \Nsimple gray robe would—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.34,0:06:46.84,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.84,0:06:48.17,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Please leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.17,0:06:48.88,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.88,0:06:50.34,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,L-Leave what to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.34,0:06:53.98,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I promise I will make you lovelier \Nthan anyone else ever could.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.98,0:06:54.98,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.19,0:07:05.36,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Now that we've made it this \Nfar, we should be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.78,0:07:07.52,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You can lower your hood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.51,0:07:13.42,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Don't worry. None of the \Ncitizens here know your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.42,0:07:15.74,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Th-That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.71,0:07:31.76,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I know exactly what you want to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.76,0:07:35.29,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I had guessed that this must \Nbe official business...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.29,0:07:37.58,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,but being dressed too plainly \Nwould stand out, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.58,0:07:41.89,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Since it's you, I thought you'd come \Nin a linen dress and plain robe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.89,0:07:44.21,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Am I really that predictable?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.21,0:07:45.74,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Is this your maid's doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.11,0:07:49.34,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Those clothes pose no problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.34,0:07:50.51,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Truly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.51,0:07:53.43,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I must give your maid my highest praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.43,0:07:54.49,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.49,0:07:54.91,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.24,0:07:56.96,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.17,0:08:08.59,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,The marketplace!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.40,0:08:12.60,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's just a marketplace, \Nthe kind you'd find anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.60,0:08:14.68,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.20,0:08:17.70,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Those are Coquito's famous grapes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.70,0:08:19.43,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Those are rare saloof bird eggs!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.43,0:08:20.96,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,And could those be—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.06,0:08:30.26,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,A-A marketplace does, of course, show \Nthe current economic conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.26,0:08:33.42,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,but it also reflects the public \Npeace of the surrounding areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.45,0:08:40.12,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,A pocket watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.59,0:08:43.74,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness? Is there something over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.74,0:08:45.33,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You want to see the marketplace, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.00,0:08:49.57,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.72,0:08:57.22,main,merchant lady,0,0,0,,What do you think? These are fresh berries!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:08:58.94,main,merchant man,0,0,0,,These are a specialty from Coyolles!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.94,0:09:01.22,main,merchant man,0,0,0,,They've just come in from Ceutena!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.22,0:09:03.38,main,merchant man,0,0,0,,Young lady, I'll give you a discount!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.36,0:09:06.73,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Sorry to keep you waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.71,0:09:08.61,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.00,0:09:10.90,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,What is that disquieting object?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.90,0:09:12.71,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,A fruit from Coyolles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.71,0:09:16.24,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It looks a little unusual, but it's very \Nnutritious, so it's good for the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.24,0:09:19.77,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I said, wait. No matter how I think \Nabout it, that appearance is—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.01,0:09:20.62,top,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's good for the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.54,0:09:32.30,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,How do you like it? It's sweeter \Nthan it looks, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.51,0:09:36.84,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It tastes like it's nutritious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.84,0:09:39.24,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,My, what a bitter expression!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.03,0:09:45.63,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,We should get moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.63,0:09:49.48,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,If we stay in one place for too long, \NOliver's deputies will find us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.52,0:09:57.73,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He isn't executing official duties today?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.62,0:10:04.88,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The proprietor here doesn't \Ncome to the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.41,0:10:08.13,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, it becomes \Nnecessary for me to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.36,0:10:17.17,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,We've been awaiting your arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.05,0:10:22.56,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,To be employed by Your Highness, the \Ncrown prince, brings us great joy and—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.56,0:10:24.91,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,No need for speeches. Raise your heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.32,0:10:28.40,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,It's an honor to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.40,0:10:33.40,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,I'm the proprietor of this \Nstore, Mihaela Laure Wehrmann.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.40,0:10:37.55,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you. My name \Nis Rishe Irmgard Weitzner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.28,0:10:43.53,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,How beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.53,0:10:46.72,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,We are humble jewelers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.72,0:10:49.47,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, among these stones,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.47,0:10:52.43,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,which do you think is a fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.43,0:10:53.42,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.98,0:10:55.11,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.11,0:10:56.15,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Try answering her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.61,0:11:13.94,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.23,0:11:16.88,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,What a clear answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.88,0:11:19.95,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,Being able to answer so \Nhonestly is a wonderful—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.95,0:11:21.57,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,So, Madam Proprietor,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.57,0:11:24.20,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,may I borrow some appraisal tools?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.20,0:11:25.02,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,Pardon me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.89,0:11:38.59,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Each one has a high degree of transparency, \Nand the cuts are very fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.72,0:11:40.74,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.37,0:11:44.22,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,These stones...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.49,0:11:46.47,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,all three of them are \Nimitations, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.89,0:11:49.52,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,I failed to recognize your skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.52,0:11:54.10,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,You are the first to request appraisal tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.40,0:11:57.82,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,That said, they truly are beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.82,0:11:59.99,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even knowing that they are imitations,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.43,0:12:06.13,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm sure there must be many people \Nwho love and care for these stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.48,0:12:09.80,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,You are...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.73,0:12:14.22,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,I find myself admiring you more and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.22,0:12:16.80,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What? Oh, but I haven't done \Nanything to warrant it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.80,0:12:21.13,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,Our merchandise in this store \Nis only sold to a select few.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.13,0:12:25.01,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,I would very much like to show you our wares.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.72,0:12:30.85,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,If you've approved of her, then \Ngive her exactly what she wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.85,0:12:33.52,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,Yes, we will ready our wares with pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.52,0:12:36.68,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What? What is going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.68,0:12:41.11,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I thought I was accompanying Your Highness \Nto fulfill your wishes, wasn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.99,0:12:43.99,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The one thing I wish from you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.71,0:12:47.12,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,is for you to allow me to \Ngift you a ring. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.12,0:12:49.12,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What? A ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.12,0:12:50.55,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,His Highness, the crown prince,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.55,0:12:54.43,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,seeks a ring to give to his bride \Nduring the wedding ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.43,0:12:56.88,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,Now, I will prepare a few things and return.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.13,0:13:00.88,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Ring? Bride?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.88,0:13:02.81,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Why? For what purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.81,0:13:06.49,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,In Galkhein, a ring shouldn't be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.49,0:13:07.89,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But more importantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.19,0:13:10.95,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,How did our sparring \Nmatch lead you to this conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.95,0:13:13.78,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,If I said, "I'll buy you a \Nring, so pick what you'd like,"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.78,0:13:17.02,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I can't imagine that you'd \Nquietly make your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.51,0:13:20.88,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You wouldn't accept others buying \Nthings to give to you, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.65,0:13:24.41,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The stones they have here are first-class.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.41,0:13:26.82,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I have no intention of letting \Nmoney be an obstacle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:30.16,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,But, Your Highness, I don't think that \NI can readily accept such a valuable—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.16,0:13:32.48,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,If you have a ring made here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.48,0:13:35.90,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,then my idle wealth, which I have no \Nmeans of using, will fall to the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.90,0:13:37.29,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It will help the economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.80,0:13:42.80,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I see. In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.80,0:13:44.60,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I shall make my choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.60,0:13:47.05,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,With utmost sincerity and \Nwith everything I have in me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.57,0:13:54.56,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,The ring will be put on me \Nduring the wedding,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.89,0:13:57.06,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,so maybe a diamond would be best?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.36,0:14:01.13,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Or, perhaps, to match my eyes... an emerald?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.14,0:14:15.14,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,I ask out of solicitude, but \Nmay I offer a suggestion?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.14,0:14:16.71,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.27,0:14:20.96,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,Putting on a favorite piece of \Njewelry and wearing it proudly...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.96,0:14:24.71,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,Just that simple action can \Nfill a girl with courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.02,0:14:28.33,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,This will become your very \Nown protective amulet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.33,0:14:31.30,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,Pick something you genuinely like.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.97,0:14:35.77,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,For example, Lady Rishe, \Nwhat color do you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.77,0:14:37.39,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What color do I like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.92,0:14:52.41,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Like crystal clear ice from a \Nfrozen sea in a cold country...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.41,0:14:53.80,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,That sort of color...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.70,0:15:01.00,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Do you have a stone here that \Nis the same color as his eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.91,0:15:09.70,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.93,0:15:13.76,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,Oh, my! My, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.76,0:15:15.28,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,No, it isn't like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.28,0:15:17.48,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What I just said didn't \Ncarry any unusual meaning!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.48,0:15:18.93,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I really have no hidden purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.93,0:15:21.96,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,it's only that I've always liked \Nthe color of Prince Arnold's eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.96,0:15:23.44,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,and thought that it's pretty, that's all!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.49,0:15:27.07,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,You've always thought that, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.07,0:15:29.04,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,If you'll wait just a moment please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.04,0:15:31.51,main,Mihaela,0,0,0,,I have something I'd like \Nto recommend to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.51,0:15:33.48,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Madam Proprietor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.13,0:15:41.58,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please, forget what just happened here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.74,0:15:50.96,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Oh, this beautiful sunset \Nis illuminating the palace!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.76,0:15:58.41,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Why the third finger of your left hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.41,0:15:59.20,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.20,0:16:02.56,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,When they measured your ring size, you \Nindicated that finger, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.01,0:16:08.94,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I suppose you say it's a \Nnotion I've always had.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.60,0:16:13.76,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Putting a ring on the third finger \Nof the left hand during the wedding
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.76,0:16:16.45,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,is the custom in the country I was born in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.88,0:16:19.78,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,But, Your Highness, why did you \Ndecide to give me a ring at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.78,0:16:23.10,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,No particular reason. And the fact that \Nit's a ring holds no specific meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.16,0:16:28.08,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,But you often work with \Nyour hands, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.90,0:16:34.04,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,To have an ornament I gave \Nyou on those fingers...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.04,0:16:36.97,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I was certain that it \Nwould make me feel good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.76,0:16:39.04,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.04,0:16:51.90,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, the morning that it's finished...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.90,0:16:53.99,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'll show you before anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.26,0:16:54.97,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.04,0:17:11.58,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.96,0:17:17.20,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, I heard \Nthat Count Lawvine had arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:19.44,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Whose guest is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.44,0:17:20.91,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I called him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.91,0:17:24.05,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,He's the best qualified person to \Ninstruct the knight candidates.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.07,0:17:28.02,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.02,0:17:31.27,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,who are you waiting for in this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.27,0:17:33.82,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,That's quite an abrupt question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.28,0:17:39.26,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Count Lawvine protects a \Nvery important location.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:43.82,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I can't imagine that you'd call him \Nhere simply to train the recruits.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.11,0:17:48.34,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,And what made you think that \NI'm waiting for someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.34,0:17:52.31,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness frequently \Nchecked your pocket watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.80,0:17:56.30,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I thought that you were concerned about \Nwhat time to return to the palace,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.30,0:18:00.18,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,but since we arrived here, you \Nhaven't once taken out your watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.59,0:18:05.73,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Additionally, this is a spot where one \Ncan observe people entering the capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.62,0:18:12.49,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The other day, a letter \Narrived from another country.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.44,0:18:15.75,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It said that the sender wouldn't \Nbe able to attend the wedding,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.75,0:18:17.82,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,so they would come to celebrate in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.91,0:18:23.33,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Before I could send a reply to say that \Nwouldn't be necessary, another letter arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.33,0:18:25.83,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It said that they wanted to \Ncelebrate as soon as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:28.29,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,so they'd leave without awaiting a reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.24,0:18:33.91,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,At the marketplace, someone was selling \Nfruit that had just arrived from Coyolles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.91,0:18:36.49,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,The sender of the letter \Nwas on that same ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.97,0:18:40.84,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Given the information from my scouts and \Nthe time it takes a carriage to travel...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.68,0:19:01.91,flashback,Kyle; previous life,0,0,0,,Weitzner,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.44,0:19:04.41,flashback,Kyle; previous life,0,0,0,,I want to protect this kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.89,0:19:11.34,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Prince Kyle...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.07,0:19:18.39,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Earlier, Kyle had an audience \Nwith His Majesty, my father,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.39,0:19:20.01,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,and he was given permission to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.64,0:19:24.28,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,As I thought, he must have a \Nparticular aim in coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.44,0:19:31.81,main,knight 2,0,0,0,,The Prince of Coyolles, His Highness Kyle \NMorgan Cleverly, is here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:38.33,main,Kyle,0,0,0,,I congratulate you on the occasion \Nof your marriage, Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.33,0:19:43.46,main,Kyle,0,0,0,,I, Kyle Morgan Cleverly, representing \Nmy father, King of Coyolles,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.46,0:19:45.84,main,Kyle,0,0,0,,hastened here to in hopes \Nof celebrating the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.84,0:19:48.49,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You have taken many pains \Nto travel all this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.49,0:19:50.66,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,For that I offer my heartfelt gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.56,0:19:55.64,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,There is a great difference in strength \Nbetween this empire and Coyolles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.50,0:19:59.68,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Coyolles is a country which \Nproduces gems, gold, and silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.68,0:20:01.55,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,They're wealthy, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.17,0:20:04.98,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,for most of the year, they're \Nvirtually cut off by snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.98,0:20:07.15,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,For food and other necessities of daily life
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.15,0:20:10.36,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,they must depend upon trade with \Ntheir neighboring countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.36,0:20:11.78,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,And five years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.78,0:20:15.14,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,they are destroyed in the war \Nthat Prince Arnold instigates.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.90,0:20:17.81,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.81,0:20:19.90,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes, Prince Arnold?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.51,0:20:24.43,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,This is Rishe, who will be my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.43,0:20:26.35,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm honored to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.35,0:20:29.16,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,My name is Rishe Irmgard Weitzner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.16,0:20:31.76,main,Kyle,0,0,0,,I am extraordinarily delighted to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.29,0:20:38.86,main,Kyle,0,0,0,,I knew that anyone who would become Prince \NArnold's wife must surely be a magnificent lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.20,0:20:47.06,main,Kyle,0,0,0,,but I never imagined anyone \Nof such a caliber as yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.66,0:20:50.18,main,Kyle,0,0,0,,You are a warm, beautiful goddess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.18,0:20:54.39,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I am undeserving of such words, Prince Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.39,0:20:56.65,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,More important than these \Nempty social pleasantries...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.39,0:20:56.65,top,Kyle; background,0,0,0,,Even the gold which my \Nkingdom is so proud of,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.93,0:20:59.60,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Prince Kyle has far too \Nlittle color in his face!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.93,0:20:59.60,top,Kyle; background,0,0,0,,is no match for the brilliance \Nemanating from you, Lady Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.60,0:21:01.95,top,Kyle; background,0,0,0,,Even flowers at the height of their \Nbeauty, blooming in profusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.60,0:21:03.53,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,His skin is already pale to begin \Nwith, but he looks nearly blue now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.95,0:21:03.53,top,Kyle; background,0,0,0,,would feel shamed in your presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.80,0:21:15.92,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Did you learn something?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.92,0:21:17.44,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I can't quite grasp it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.44,0:21:19.06,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Everything he said was innocuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.06,0:21:20.92,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,He didn't show even a sliver \Nof his true intentions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.92,0:21:21.60,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.60,0:21:25.30,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, earlier, the look you had, like you \Nwere about to kill with your gaze...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.30,0:21:26.57,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.30,0:21:32.28,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,More importantly, Kyle seems to have brought\N a number of academics from Coyolles.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.28,0:21:33.06,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.21,0:21:37.04,flashback,Michel; previous life,0,0,0,,Your color has improved tremendously, Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.50,0:21:40.95,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,It couldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.11,0:21:45.13,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,If you want to hear what they have \Nto say, too, I'll make arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.85,0:21:47.39,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I would be happy to!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.39,0:21:50.95,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Actually, I've heard that \NPrince Kyle is very weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.95,0:21:53.66,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,and I have a medicine \NI'd like for him to try!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.66,0:21:56.30,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,If the scholars he has \Nwith him will permit it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.30,0:21:59.08,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,then there won't be any need \Nto slip the drug into his food!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.21,0:22:02.75,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,That was a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.75,0:22:05.63,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It didn't sound like a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.63,0:22:09.56,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,First, tomorrow there will be a welcome \Nfeast for him, though it will be a bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.56,0:22:12.26,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Of course. I will have the preparations made.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.26,0:22:15.27,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I'll have Kyle and Lawvine \Nmeet face-to-face there.
